:{{see|Virus}}
==English==

===Etymology===
The word '''virus''' is derived from the [[Latin]] <i>virus</i>, meaning roughly "poison", "slime" or "venom", and still retains this meaning.

===Noun===
'''virus'''  (''plural:'' '''[[viruses]]''')
# A core of [[DNA]] or [[RNA]] surrounded by a [[protein]] coat that requires a living cell to [[replicate]] &mdash; often causes disease in the host organism.
# A [[computer virus]]; often mistakenly used where [[malware]] would be the correct word.

===External links===
*An article on the [[Wikipedia:Plural of virus|plural of ''virus'']].

